net.objectzoo.delegates
Interface ActionAsyncResult

All Known Subinterfaces:
FuncAsyncResult<R>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AsyncFutureTask
public interface ActionAsyncResult

A ActionAsyncResult represents the result of an ActionAsync invocation. Methods are provided to check if the invocation is complete, to wait for its completion and check the outcome. The outcome can be checked using the method endInvoke() when the ActionAsync has completed, blocking if necessary until it is ready. Cancellation is performed by the cancel(boolean) method. Additional methods are provided to determine if the ActionAsync completed normally or was cancelled. Once an ActionAsync has completed, the ActionAsync cannot be cancelled.

Author:
tilmann

cancel

boolean cancel(boolean mayInterruptIfRunning)
Attempts to cancel the invocation of this ActionAsync. This attempt will fail if the ActionAsync has already completed, has already been cancelled, or could not be cancelled for some other reason. If successful, and this ActionAsync has not started when cancel(boolean) is called, this ActionAsync should never run. If the ActionAsync has already started, then the mayInterruptIfRunning parameter determines whether the thread executing this ActionAsync should be interrupted in an attempt to stop the ActionAsync. After this method returns, subsequent calls to isDone() will always return true. Subsequent calls to isCancelled() will always return true if this method returned true.

Parameters:
mayInterruptIfRunning - true if the thread executing this ActionAsync should be interrupted; otherwise, in-progress ActionAsyncs are allowed to complete
Returns:
false if the ActionAsync could not be cancelled, typically because it has already completed normally; true otherwise

isCancelled

boolean isCancelled()
Returns true if this ActionAsync was cancelled before it completed normally.

Returns:
true if this ActionAsync was cancelled before it completed

isDone

boolean isDone()
Returns true if this ActionAsync completed. Completion may be due to normal termination, an exception, or cancellation -- in all of these cases, this method will return true.

Returns:
true if this ActionAsync completed
